## Build

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
. .venv/bin/activate
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
```bash
npm install
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
```bash
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- end }}

## Codex

1. Put repository instructions in `AGENTS.md`.
2. Keep project-local Codex settings in `.codex/config.toml`.
3. The generated executable handles the documented `notify` hook.

Hook output on stdout must stay reserved for Codex wire responses. Write diagnostics to stderr only.

{{- if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
On Windows, the shell runtime requires `bash` in `PATH`.
{{- end }}

{{- if eq .Runtime "node" }}
TypeScript is supported through a build step that emits JavaScript for the `node` runtime entrypoint. This scaffold stays JS-first.
{{- end }}
